    "causal_summary": "Cocoindex currently encodes embeddings via sentence-transformers on PyTorch. On macOS that routes through Metal Performance Shaders, which targets the GPU and cannot reach Apple's Neural Engine. On Windows without CUDA, PyTorch is CPU-only, leaving AMD and Intel GPUs idle. Both gaps can increase fan ramp, indexing time, and query latency relative to the host silicon.",
